### Node.js Agent: API Error Handling with Callbacks

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

In version 4.12.0, error handling in Node.js `CollectorAPI` and `RemoteMethod` was converted to use callbacks instead of throwing errors. This change aligns with asynchronous error handling patterns and prevents potential agent crashes that could occur when errors were thrown, such as exceeding payload size limits.

```javascript
// Previous behavior (throwing errors):
// RemoteMethod._safeRequest(options, function(err, res) {
//   if (err) throw err;
//   // ... process response
// });

// New behavior (handling errors in callback):
RemoteMethod._safeRequest(options, function(err, res) {
  if (err) {
    // Handle the error gracefully here
    console.error('Request failed:', err);
    return;
  }
  // ... process response
});
```

