### Fixing Null Error Handling in Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This example addresses an issue where the Node.js agent could crash if `null` was thrown instead of an `Error` object. The fix ensures robust error handling even in such scenarios.

```javascript
// Original problematic code (conceptual)
try {
  // ... some operation that might throw null ...
} catch (e) {
  if (e === null) {
    // Agent could crash here
  }
}

// Fixed behavior (conceptual)
try {
  // ... some operation that might throw null ...
} catch (e) {
  if (e === null) {
    // Agent handles null gracefully
  }
}
```

