### Handle Immutable/Frozen Error Objects - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Version v1.22.0 includes a fix to handle immutable and frozen error objects gracefully. Previously, the agent would crash when attempting to tag these objects with the current transaction. This improvement ensures stability when dealing with such error types.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

try {
  // Code that might throw an immutable or frozen error
  throw Object.freeze({});
} catch (err) {
  // The agent will now handle this without crashing
  newrelic.noticeError(err);
}
```

