### Handle Uncaught Exceptions - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

In v1.21.2, the agent's handling of uncaught exceptions was corrected, particularly for Node versions without `process._fatalException` (like v0.8). The agent now correctly records the error and passes it to other registered handlers, preventing inverted behavior.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
  // The New Relic agent will now properly record and forward this error.
  console.error('Caught exception: ' + err);
  // The agent ensures this error is handled by other handlers if present.
});

// Simulate an uncaught exception
setTimeout(() => {
  throw new Error('This is an uncaught exception');
}, 1000);
```

