### Node.js: Handling Unhandled Promise Rejections in Lambda

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet addresses an issue where unhandled promise rejections were not logged as errors within AWS Lambda executions using the New Relic Node.js agent. It highlights the importance of robust error handling for asynchronous operations in serverless environments.

```javascript
// Example of how to catch and log unhandled promise rejections:
process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason, promise) => {
  console.error('Unhandled Rejection at:', promise, 'reason:', reason);
  // Use New Relic's API to report this as an error if not already handled
  // newrelic.noticeError(reason);
});

// Example of a promise that might cause an unhandled rejection if not caught:
// const potentiallyFailingPromise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
//   setTimeout(() => {
//     reject(new Error('Something went wrong in the promise'));
//   }, 1000);
// });

// If the promise rejection is not handled elsewhere, the 'unhandledRejection' event will fire.
```

