### Marking Expected Errors - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Version 9.12.1 enhanced the `noticeError` function by allowing developers to mark errors as expected. By passing `true` as the last argument, errors will not impact error metrics or Apdex scores, useful for handling known, non-critical errors.

```javascript
// With custom attributes
newrelic.noticeError(error, { custom: 'attributes' }, true);

// Without custom attributes
newrelic.noticeError(error, true);
```

