### Customizing Error Group Names - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Version 9.14.0 introduced the `setErrorGroupCallback` API function, allowing developers to customize the `error.group.name` attribute. This enables more granular control over how errors are grouped in the Errors Inbox, improving error monitoring and triage.

```javascript
newrelic.setErrorGroupCallback((error, transaction) => {
  return 'custom-group-name';
});
```

