### Node.js Director Instrumentation Handling Null Route Handlers

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet addresses an issue in the Node.js agent's Director instrumentation where it would crash if a null route handler was provided. The updated instrumentation now correctly handles such cases, preventing crashes.

```javascript
// Assume 'newrelic' is required and configured
// Assume 'director' is used for routing

const router = new Router();

// Previously, if a route handler was null, the agent's director instrumentation would crash.
// Example of a route definition that might cause issues:
// router.get('/some/path', null);

// With the fix, the agent correctly handles null route handlers without crashing.
// The instrumentation will proceed without error, and no metrics will be generated for this specific null handler.
```

